"# Product Requirements Document — RetroForge

## Target Audience
- Retro gaming enthusiasts
- Emulator developers
- Game preservationists

## Problem Statement
Retro gaming enthusiasts struggle to find modern, cross-platform emulators that work seamlessly in the browser without complex setup or dedicated hardware.

## User Flow
- **Story 1:** As a retro gamer, I want to load ROMs and play classic games in my browser.
- **Story 2:** As a gamer, I want to save and load my progress at any point.
- **Story 3:** As a power user, I want to configure controller mappings for different platforms.

## MVP Scope
- ROM loading and parsing for NES/SNES/Game Boy
- Emulation core with CPU, GPU, and audio
- Save state creation and loading
- Controller configuration UI
- ROM library with grid view

## Future Extensions
- _RetroForge future extensions — to be refined during project review._
"
`;

exports[`Golden Test Suite — Documentation Generator > generates documentation files for RetroForge > README-md-retroforge 1`] = `
"# RetroForge

> Web-based retro game emulator for classic console experiences

## Overview
A browser-based retro game emulator that supports NES, SNES, and Game Boy platforms. Features include ROM loading, save state management, controller configuration, and cheat code support. Built with WebAssembly for high-performance emulation.

## Problem
Retro gaming enthusiasts struggle to find modern, cross-platform emulators that work seamlessly in the browser without complex setup or dedicated hardware.

## Solution
A web-based emulator platform that brings classic console gaming to any modern browser with save states, controller support, and a clean library management interface.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend:** React, Vite, Tailwind CSS
- **Other:** TypeScript, C++, WebAssembly, Emscripten, SDL2, OpenGL, IndexedDB

## MVP
- ROM loading and parsing for NES/SNES/Game Boy
- Emulation core with CPU, GPU, and audio
- Save state creation and loading
- Controller configuration UI
- ROM library with grid view

## Getting Started
_Setup instructions for RetroForge — to be added during implementation._

## Roadmap
- **Foundation & Setup** ← CURRENT
  - [ ] Initialize project with chosen tech stack
  - [ ] Set up emulator core integration
  - [ ] Configure ROM loading and file management
- **Core Emulation Features**
  - [ ] Build game library with metadata scraping
  - [ ] Implement emulator core with save states
  - [ ] Add controller mapping and input handling
- **User Experience**
  - [ ] Build save state management UI
  - [ ] Implement cheat code support
  - [ ] Add display filters and scaling options
- **Advanced Features & Launch**
  - [ ] Add multiplayer/netplay support
  - [ ] Implement achievement system
  - [ ] Add monitoring, testing, and production deployment
"
`;

exports[`Golden Test Suite — Documentation Generator > generates documentation files for RetroForge > SPEC-md-retroforge 1`] = `
"# Technical Specification — RetroForge

## Requirements
A browser-based retro game emulator that supports NES, SNES, and Game Boy platforms. Features include ROM loading, save state management, controller configuration, and cheat code support. Built with WebAssembly for high-performance emulation.

## Non-goals
- WebAssembly-based emulation core
- IndexedDB for ROM and save state storage
- Offline-capable after initial load

## Architecture
- **Pattern:** Desktop application with plugin-based emulator cores and local file storage

### Component Tree
\`\`\`
App
├── HomePage
├── GameLibraryPage
├── EmulatorCorePage
├── RomManagerPage
├── SaveStatePage
├── ControllerConfigPage
├── SettingsPage
├── ROMLoadingAndParsingForNESSNESGameBoy
├── EmulationCoreWithCPUGPUAndAudio
├── SaveStateCreationAndLoading
├── ControllerConfigurationUI
├── ROMLibraryWithGridView
\`\`\`

### Data Flow
\`\`\`
User launches app → browses game library → selects ROM → emulator core loads → game renders with audio/video → user plays with mapped controls → save state created → progress persisted
\`\`\`

## Data Model
### Entities
- **ROM**: Game ROM file for emulation
- **SaveState**: Saved game state snapshot
- **Game**: Retro game instance
- **ControllerConfig**: Controller mapping configuration
- **EmulatorCore**: Emulation core engine

## Quality Gates
- ROM files must be validated before loading
- Save states must be portable across sessions
- **Code style:** TypeScript strict mode, C++ with modern standards
- **Testing:** Unit tests for emulation core; integration tests for UI
- **Fallback behavior:** Empty sections render a helpful hint instead of crashing
"
`;

